<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">As of about three weeks ago, a plausible=C2=A0=
model of FTX Trading Ltd. and its affiliated trading firm Alameda Research=
=C2=A0would have been:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">FTX and Alameda make=C2=A0a lot of mo=
ney.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Is there something fishy abou=
t that?</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The standard sorts of theories would be along =
the lines of =E2=80=9CAlameda and FTX supposedly operated independently, bu=
t they seemed to all be friends and live together, so=C2=A0maybe Alameda ha=
d privileged access to FTX=E2=80=99s order flow and so could make unusually=
 profitable trades,=E2=80=9D something like that. In fact, though, the stor=
y seems to have been more like:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Alameda actually=C2=A0<em>lost </em>a=
 ton of money.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Then it used FTX cu=
stomer money to cover its losses.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you believed that Alameda was suspiciously=
=C2=A0profitable, and you pursued that hunch, would that have led you to th=
e truth, which is that Alameda was suspiciously=C2=A0<em>unprofitable</em>?=
 Maybe? Some of your intuitions =E2=80=94=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cthe boundaries betw=
een FTX and Alameda are more porous than they claim=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=C2=
=A0would have served you well in uncovering the truth. Others =E2=80=94=C2=
=A0=E2=80=9CAlameda makes a lot of money trading=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0wo=
uld not have.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Similarly, if you believed that FTX was violat=
ing the Bank Secrecy Act, would that have pointed you to the real problems?=
 <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29776711.281548/a=
HR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTEtMjEvdXMtcHJv=
c2VjdXRvcnMtb3BlbmVkLXByb2JlLW9mLWZ0eC1tb250aHMtYmVmb3JlLWl0cy1jb2xsYXBzZT9=
jbXBpZD1CQkQxMTIyMjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bm=
V3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjExMjImdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07cee=
f4b8524a319a23cBe117a919" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" ta=
rget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; =
border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style=
: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  Apparently not</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The US Attorney=E2=80=99s Office for the South=
ern District of New York, led by Damian Williams, spent several months work=
ing on a sweeping examination of crypto currency platforms with US and offs=
hore arms and had started poking into FTX=E2=80=99s massive exchange operat=
ions, according to people familiar with the investigation.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The focus was on compliance with the Bank Secr=
ecy Act, the people said. Authorities have used the law, requiring financia=
l institutions take steps to prevent money laundering and terrorism financi=
ng, to go after crypto platforms that allegedly falsely claimed that they d=
on=E2=80=99t serve US customers. Bahamas-based FTX operated one of the worl=
d=E2=80=99s largest international crypto exchanges, as well as a separate a=
nd much more limited venue called FTX US that said it complies with the act=
.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It=E2=80=99s unclear whether prosecutors in Ma=
nhattan reached any conclusion in their probe before FTX -- valued at nearl=
y $32 billion in a January financing -- collapsed, sending the crypto marke=
t into a dive and raising questions about the accuracy of its pledges to sa=
feguard customer assets. That put the federal investigation into a new traj=
ectory, the people said.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Of all the illegal things an offshore crypto e=
xchange could do, accepting deposits from US customers is the most obvious =
one to worry about. If you were an ambitious prosecutor and you called up F=
TX and said =E2=80=9Cwe need you to prove that you don=E2=80=99t accept US =
customers,=E2=80=9D would you have learned anything interesting about FTX=
=E2=80=99s=C2=A0<em>other=C2=A0</em>problems? One thing that we have <a hre=
f=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29776711.281548/aHR0cHM6=
Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTEtMjEvdXMtcHJvc2VjdXR=
vcnMtb3BlbmVkLXByb2JlLW9mLWZ0eC1tb250aHMtYmVmb3JlLWl0cy1jb2xsYXBzZT9jbXBpZD=
1CQkQxMTIyMjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xld=
HRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjExMjImdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524=
a319a23cCe117a919" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D=
"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-=
bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid=
; background-color: #ccc;">  all</a> learned <a href=3D"https://link.mail.b=
loombergbusiness.com/click/29776711.281548/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNv=
bS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTEtMjEva2VlcGluZy10cmFjay1vZi1jcnlwdG8taXM=
taGFyZD9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMTIyMjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3=
VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjExMjImdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/6=
07f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB29b46819" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"items=
cope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !imp=
ortant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bott=
om-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  recently</a> is that FTX=E2=80=
=99s record-keeping was a mess, in ways that might have caused or at least =
encouraged the misuse of customer funds. If you called up FTX and said =E2=
=80=9Cprove that you don=E2=80=99t accept US customers=E2=80=9D and FTX sai=
d to you =E2=80=9Chmm, interesting, you want a list of our customers? Not s=
ure we have that anywhere,=E2=80=9D that might have raised additional, non-=
Bank-Secrecy-Act-related red flags. =E2=80=9CWait now that I have you here,=
 prove that you actually have your customers=E2=80=99 money,=E2=80=9D would=
 have been a reasonable follow-up question, when you saw the disarray of FT=
X=E2=80=99s records.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the other hand, if you are a New York feder=
al prosecutor, and you=C2=A0<em>can=E2=80=99t=C2=A0</em>find a Bank Secrecy=
 Act violation, maybe you don=E2=80=99t care about the rest? If FTX wasn=E2=
=80=99t handling money for US customers then why should a US prosecutor car=
e if it was also misusing the money? I am pretty sure we=E2=80=99ll get ans=
wers to those questions soon enough.</p>
