investigations that failed to find problems at FTX</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Bain &amp; Co. was among consulting firms that=
 helped conduct due diligence for Tiger Global Management=E2=80=99s investm=
ent in now-defunct crypto exchange FTX, according to people familiar with t=
he matter.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Tiger Global, which pays Bain more than $100 m=
illion a year to research private companies, has now written down its $38 m=
illion FTX stake to zero, the people said. Sam Bankman-Fried=E2=80=99s over=
sight of a vast web of FTX-linked entities was one of the risks highlighted=
 during the due-diligence process, but the money manager still believed it =
was a sound investment at the time, one of the people said. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Tiger Global=E2=80=99s FTX investment was a ti=
ny portion of its $12.7 billion Private Investment Partners 15 fund. The fi=
rm first backed FTX in October 2021, when the crypto exchange was valued at=
 $25 billion, and again in January at a $32.5 billion valuation, according =
to PitchBook data.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The FTX bet was one of 358 venture capital inv=
estments Tiger Global made last year, and one of 290 so far in 2022, accord=
ing to PitchBook.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Tiger Global called Bain and was like =E2=80=
=9Chey guys, drop everything, we are thinking of investing 0.3% of our fund=
 in a giant crypto exchange that makes a billion dollars a year and has Tom=
 Brady as a spokesman, do you think that=E2=80=99s a good idea,=E2=80=9D an=
d Bain dropped everything to investigate FTX, and then 20 minutes later Tig=
er Global called back and was like =E2=80=9Chey guys, drop everything, we a=
re thinking of investing 0.4% of our fund in a pre-revenue dog treat delive=
ry service,=E2=80=9D and Bain was like =E2=80=9Ceh I=E2=80=99m sure FTX is =
fine, you said dog treat delivery?=E2=80=9D Tiger Global=C2=A0closed one in=
vestment a day last year! They <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusine=
ss.com/click/29776711.281548/aHR0cHM6Ly9uaWNrc3R1YXJ0LnN1YnN0YWNrLmNvbS9wL3=
