<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Now that Elon Musk has invited Donald Trump ba=
ck on Twitter, is it securities fraud for Trump to tweet? Possibly? But als=
o it might be securities fraud if he <em>didn=E2=80=99t </em>tweet, and the=
n started tweeting later? The problem=C2=A0is that Trump is committed to Tr=
uth Social, the social media ghost town of Trump Media &amp; Technology Gro=
up, which has a long-delayed deal to go public by merging=C2=A0with Digital=
 World Acquisition Corp.=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusines=
s.com/click/29776711.281548/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VtYWZvci5jb20vYXJ0aWNsZS8xMS8=
wMi8yMDIyL2RvbmFsZC10cnVtcHMtcXVlc3QtdG8tYnVpbGQtYS1uZXctdHdpdHRlci13b3VsZC=
1jb21wbGljYXRlLWEtcmV0dXJuLXRvLXRoZS1vbGQtb25l/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB6ad=
c6096" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" sty=
le=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width=
: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background=
-color: #ccc;">Semafor reports</a>:=C2=A0</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Trump has repeatedly said he's happy with his =
own Truth Social site and won=E2=80=99t return, but given his relationship =
to both Twitter and the truth it's done little to dampen speculation that h=
e=E2=80=99d resume his dominant place on the central platform. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Since Trump is a core part of Truth Social=E2=
=80=99s value, rejoining Twitter could create some potential legal complica=
tions, according to Eric Talley, a professor at Columbia Law School who spe=
cializes in corporate law.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In particular, if Trump repeatedly signals in =
public before a merger that he=E2=80=99s never joining Twitter, then closes=
 a SPAC deal and reneges, some shareholders could decide they were misled.<=
/p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CIf it=E2=80=99s going to look, later =
on, that he never had that intention=E2=80=9D of remaining off Twitter =E2=
=80=9Cbut he just wanted to convince people that they should go ahead and c=
lose [the SPAC deal] that=E2=80=99s kind of a textbook securities fraud law=
suit,=E2=80=9D Talley said.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If Trump does decide to rejoin Twitter without=
 incident, his deal could affect how he uses the service. An SEC filing by =
TMTG notes that the former president =E2=80=9Cis generally obligated to mak=
e any social media post on TruthSocial and may not make the same post on an=
other social media site for 6 hours=E2=80=9D through at least June 22, 2023=
. That date is notably the exact same point in the 2016 cycle when Trump de=
clared his presidential run.</p>
</blockquote>
